Always seek professional guidance for property-specific or tax-related queries.Can I avail top up loan on my current home loan for renovation/ home furnishing?Yes, a top-up loan is an additional loan amount that your lender may offer over and above your existing home loan.It is typically:
Secured against the same property.Offered at interest rates similar to or slightly higher than your home loan.Easier to process due to your existing relationship with the lender.To qualify, you generally need:
An active home loan with the lender.A good repayment track record.Sufficient equity in the property (i.e., the outstanding loan should be within a certain percentage of the property’s value).A stable income and good credit score.Content source: Provided document uploaded by the user.:contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}

